<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS PUT ON SECOND-LANGUAGE PERFORMANCES
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  April 21 (CNA) 04/21/07  18:11:28 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
Taipei City's public and private senior high schools held a joint
exhibition of assignments and performances by students in
different languages Saturday to showcase their achievements in
learning a second foreign language.
</P>
<P>
Performances were staged at three municipal senior high schools,
including performances in German, Spanish and Korean at Taipei
Municipal Sungshan Senior High School, where students wore the
traditional costumes of different countries to present either
plays or singing to the audience.
</P>
<P>
Performances in French and Latin were staged at Taipei Municipal
Hsisung Senior High School, with more than 2,000 students from 27
schools enrolled in French courses participating, and students
from the Taipei Municipal First Girl's High School, which is the
only school in the city that offers a Latin course.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, performances in Japanese, the language being learned
by the most students in Taipei City, were held at Taipei
Municipal Chunglun Senior High School, including tea ceremony and
flower arrangement demonstrations and a kimono fashion show.
</P>
